<TITLE> Badda people set up independence memorial </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 28 (bdnews24.com) Residents of Bhatara Union under Badda Police Station have set up a memorial at Tek Shaoratala area to mark Independence Day. Professor Kabir Chowdhury will formally inaugurate the memorial styled "Birer Prottabartyan" (Return of the hero) at 4.00pm Saturday. Sudeepta Mallick is the architect of the 61-foot high memorial. The history of independence struggle of the country from 1857 to the Liberation War in 1971 and portraits of the independence heroes have been inscribed on the body of the monument. A library with books on the Liberation War and a museum have been set up at the altar of the monument. bdnews24
